Citation.sTitle: Thermodynamics of biofuels: Excess enthalpies for binary mixtures involving ethyl 1,1-dimethylethyl ether and hydrocarbons at different temperatures using a new flow calorimeter
Citation.sAbstract: Excess molar enthalpies for the binary systems: (ethyl 1,1-dimethylethyl ether + heptane); (ethyl 1,1- dimethylethyl ether + cyclohexane); (ethyl 1,1-dimethylethyl ether + toluene); (cyclohexane + toluene), and (toluene + heptane) have been measured at T = (298.15 and 313.15) K using a new isothermal flow calorimeter developed in the laboratory. The technique was previously checked by measuring test systems. The experimental results have been correlated with the Redlich Kister polynomial equation. The mixing effects observed and the influence of the temperature are discussed.
